Now we solve the system of linear equations. We can eliminate $\mu$ by rearranging both equations to $\mu = \dots$ or by subtraction.

$$
\begin{aligned}
60 &= \mu - 0.8416\sigma && \text{(Equation 1)} \\
85 &= \mu + 0.6745\sigma && \text{(Equation 2)}
\end{aligned}
$$

Subtract Equation 1 from Equation 2:

$$
\begin{aligned}
(85 - 60) &= (\mu - \mu) + (0.6745\sigma - (-0.8416\sigma)) \\
25 &= 1.5161\sigma \\
\sigma &= \frac{25}{1.5161} \approx 16.489...
\end{aligned}
$$
